    <note>Zhu(1) Shaolian [13180] According to Hu Quan, WJ, 25.7a, citing the lineage or family genealogy of the Zhu (jiapu), Shaolian was recruited by the Tang founder on the basis of a reputation for filial piety and righteousness. He appears, however, in the genealogical tables of XTS, 74B.20a in a position which would indicate a late Tang person and with no office indicated. I am arbitrarily accepting the earlier date. His descendants moved to Jian-s. The move of one branch (it seems this one) of the Peiguo Zhu is also recorded in XTS.</note>
